<subSubSection id="F6110454833997A5C342CA49230A0839" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FF390AF9164171EBFD677D8A5279FE00" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="50B2148FE29B9F386C4FA05E0DC46094" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="C08A02CECA693A8524D9B3A2EB148B23" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum mammosum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mammosum">
<emphasis id="5CA6FA5ECD3D8C3845A88E921138EDD2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum mammosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded from China, Myanmar, the Philippines, Thailand, and Vietnam, but is almost certainly more widespread in the region; it is native to southern South America and is widely cultivated for ornament.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
